# Push to GitHub

After completing any implementation or fix in this repo:

1. Commit all relevant changes with a clear message focused on why.
2. Push to `origin/main` unless the user specifies another branch.
3. Do this automatically at the end of the task — do not wait for the user to ask.
4. Skip commit/push only when there are no file changes, or the user explicitly says not to push.

Use the project's git safety protocol: never force-push to main, never skip hooks, never commit secrets.
